results.contract_name: Statement of Work between Unilever U.K.Central Resources Ltd & Ernst & Young LLP for project ML enabled Demand Forecasting
key_terms: Project Code: ML enabled Demand Forecasting
Functional Scope: Project will be led by Global I&A Director
Technical Scope: EY Team will work with Unilever Team
Models which will include Total Volume Forecast, Baseline, Long Term Forecast
Granularity of the Model will be at GTIN – Customer Planning - Week Level
All models will be developed using Python and on Azure Databricks
The success criteria for the would be according to the one mentioned in the approved BOSCARD
Mandatory Data: Sales data, Product mappings, Customer mappings, GTIN transitions, GTIN delisting, Demand planner data, Promo data, Holiday data, APG mapping
Optional Data: Dispatch rate, Pricing information
The integration with Kinaxis schema will be done with FEU outputs
Lead Allocation from EY for every Market will be done in collaboration with Unilever
External data like weather, holiday calendar needs to be provided by Unilever
Project is closed once the PGLS phase of 4 weeks is completed

The contract is effective from March 2023 and expires in June 2023. The parent contract is CW67101.
